.TH OPENTELEMETRY-JAVA 1 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-java-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-java \- OpenTelemetry Java Auto-Instrumentation Agent
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Java Auto-Instrumentation Agent automatically instruments
Java applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs.
.PP
When installed alongside
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8),
Java applications are automatically instrumented without code changes.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/java/otel-config.yaml
Default configuration file for the Java agent.
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/java.conf
Drop-in configuration that registers the Java agent with the injector.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/opentelemetry/java/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
The Java agent JAR file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
OTLP endpoint (default: http://localhost:4317).
.TP
.B OTEL_JAVAAGENT_ENABLED
Set to "false" to disable (default: true).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8)
.PP
https://opentelemetry.io/docs/zero-code/java/agent/
